description: Demolition of existing buildings and erection of part 4 to part 10 storey buildings providing for 1,195sqm of A1/A2/A3/B1 (commercial / office) floor space, 5430sqm of B1 (office) floor space, 200sqm of D1 (community) floor space, 274 flats with reception concierge, 58 car parking spaces, 300 cycle spaces and associated access and landscaping.
decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  Notwithstanding the plans hereby approved, details of a scheme of screening or other such design feature that would prevent the direct overlooking of existing habitable room windows within 46-58 Peartree Street shall be submitted to an approved in writing by Local Planning Authority, and installed, prior to the first occupation of the development hereby approved.  

The development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter and no change there from shall take place without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority.

REASON:  To ensure that the development would not cause a significant or undue loss of privacy to the existing residential properties at Peartree Street.
